						               													<description>Papecarz is  a &amp;quot;roll and move&amp;quot; racing game,  a mix of strategy, placement &amp;amp; luck.&amp;#10;Two to six players control racing cars competing to win a single 8 lap race or a series of races.&amp;#10;As a driver, the player has to cunningly calculate every single move to make the most of the Caution Flags, restart, Slingshot Passes, Pushing and Shunting.&amp;#10;While as a crew chief, the player has to plan an effective and flexible race strategy and keep an eagle eye on the opponent's  tactics.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The race is made up of four main phases:&amp;#10;-Pre start: you choose your setup and decide the start grid.&amp;#10;-Start: you want to try to get a good position straight away.&amp;#10;-First 7 laps: here you need to get as many Boost points as you can and try to avoid the Damage cards.&amp;#10;-Last lap: put the pedal to the metal! it&amp;rsquo;s your chance to cross the finish line first and win the race.&amp;#10;At the end of each lap you get a card depending on your position; the higher your position, the better your card.&amp;#10;1st: one White card =2 Boost points&amp;#10;2nd &amp;amp; 3rd: one green card =1 Boost points&amp;#10;4th &amp;amp; 5th: one brown card =damage (Watch out! you could be in trouble!)&amp;#10;6th: one black card= serious damage (Oh no! you're in big trouble!)&amp;#10;And when you pit, this is where your strategy comes in;  each car has two possible setups.&amp;#10;It's the setup that tells you how many cards and kinds of cards you can turn over and convert.&amp;#10;Your setup also tells you when you can take a risk and roll the dice.&amp;#10;if the car in first place fails a dice roll...the yellow flag come out: CAUTION!&amp;#10;The race restarts  with all the cars now bunched up together and some player starts cursing , while other players cheer (Yeah!); It all depends on your pit strategy!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
